#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn40.3"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn40.3:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 40 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 40 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn40.3:0.2"
msgid "1. Moggallānavagga "
msgstr "1. By Moggallāna "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 3. Tatiyajhānapañhāsutta → sukhasuttaṃ (bj) | sukhena (pts1)
msgctxt "sn40.3:0.3"
msgid "3. Tatiyajhānapañhāsutta "
msgstr "3. A Question About the Third Absorption "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn40.3:1.1"
msgid "“‘Tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ, tatiyaṃ jhānan’ti vuccati. "
msgstr "“They speak of this thing called the ‘third absorption’. "

msgctxt "sn40.3:1.2"
msgid "Katamaṃ nu kho tatiyaṃ jhānanti? "
msgstr "What is the third absorption? "

msgctxt "sn40.3:1.3"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, āvuso, etadahosi—"
msgstr "It occurred to me: "

msgctxt "sn40.3:1.4"
msgid "idha bhikkhu pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati sato ca sampajāno sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedeti, yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti: ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "‘With the fading away of rapture, a mendicant enters and remains in the third absorption, where they meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, “Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss.” "

msgctxt "sn40.3:1.5"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati tatiyaṃ jhānanti. "
msgstr "This is called the third absorption.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn40.3:1.6"
msgid "So khvāhaṃ, āvuso, pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharāmi sato ca sampajāno sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedemi. Yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti: ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharāmi. "
msgstr "And so … I was entering and remaining in the third absorption. "

msgctxt "sn40.3:1.7"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, āvuso, iminā vihārena viharato pītisahagatā saññāmanasikārā samudācaranti. "
msgstr "While I was in that meditation, perceptions and attentions accompanied by rapture beset me. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.265, sc2
msgctxt "sn40.3:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho maṃ, āvuso, bhagavā iddhiyā upasaṅkamitvā etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha came up to me with his psychic power and said, "

msgctxt "sn40.3:2.2"
msgid "‘moggallāna, moggallāna. "
msgstr "‘Moggallāna, Moggallāna! "

msgctxt "sn40.3:2.3"
msgid "Mā, brāhmaṇa, tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ pamādo, tatiye jhāne cittaṃ saṇṭhapehi, tatiye jhāne cittaṃ ekodiṃ karohi, tatiye jhāne cittaṃ samādahā’ti. "
msgstr "Don’t neglect the third absorption, brahmin! Settle your mind in the third absorption; unify your mind and immerse it in the third absorption.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn40.3:2.4"
msgid "So khvāhaṃ, āvuso, aparena samayena pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharāmi sato ca sampajāno sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedemi, yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti: ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihāsiṃ. "
msgstr "And so, after some time … I entered and remained in the third absorption. "

msgctxt "sn40.3:2.5"
msgid "Yañhi taṃ āvuso sammā vadamāno vadeyya … pe … mahābhiññataṃ patto”ti. "
msgstr "So if anyone should be rightly called a disciple who attained to great direct knowledge with help from the Teacher, it’s me.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn40.3:2.6"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

